# =================================================================
# Nintendo Switch Contest - Environment Variables
# =================================================================

# Frontend Environment Variables (VITE prefix for browser access)
# These are exposed to the browser, so never put secrets here
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_51234567890abcdef...

# Backend Environment Variables (for Vercel Functions)
# These are kept secret on the server
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_51234567890abcdef...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_1234567890abcdef...

# =================================================================
# Setup Instructions:
# =================================================================

# 1. SUPABASE SETUP:
#    - Create account at https://supabase.com
#    - Create new project
#    - Go to Settings > API
#    - Copy Project URL and anon/public key
#    - Copy service_role key (keep this secret!)

# 2. STRIPE SETUP:
#    - Create account at https://stripe.com  
#    - Go to Developers > API Keys
#    - Copy Publishable key (pk_test_...)
#    - Copy Secret key (sk_test_...)
#    - Create webhook endpoint at Developers > Webhooks
#    - Copy webhook secret (whsec_...)

# 3. VERCEL DEPLOYMENT:
#    - Add all these variables in Vercel Dashboard
#    - Go to Project Settings > Environment Variables
#    - Add each variable for Production environment

# =================================================================
# Security Notes:
# =================================================================
# - Never commit .env files to version control
# - VITE_ variables are public (visible in browser)
# - Service role keys have admin access - keep secure
# - Use test keys during development
# - Switch to live keys only for production
